WEBVTT

00:29.259 --> 00:30.302
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:33.388 --> 00:35.014
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

00:35.015 --> 00:36.308
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

00:37.684 --> 00:38.685
I found you.

00:46.777 --> 00:47.819
This is bad.

01:08.507 --> 01:10.133
Why are you…

01:11.218 --> 01:12.552
I'm just copying you.

01:14.554 --> 01:17.099
I have a habit of copying other people.

01:21.687 --> 01:24.898
-  But I can't breathe…
- Oh.

01:26.400 --> 01:27.483
Sorry.

01:29.611 --> 01:32.572
You said you hug people
you're happy to see.

01:41.957 --> 01:43.749
EPISODE 7

02:18.535 --> 02:19.995
We're here.

02:21.830 --> 02:22.831
Sir?

02:23.665 --> 02:24.708
Yes?

02:31.423 --> 02:32.923
Can you open the trunk?

02:32.924 --> 02:35.761
Just keep riding this to SHIM.
Mr. Park will be waiting.

02:49.733 --> 02:50.734
Ah.

02:51.485 --> 02:52.652
Yes, Mr. Yeon.

02:53.236 --> 02:54.487
Producer Ben?

02:54.488 --> 02:55.988
He just informed me

02:55.989 --> 02:58.074
that the collaboration project
will resume.

03:01.161 --> 03:02.287
Huh?

03:05.499 --> 03:08.083
The animation team
will return to Korea soon.

03:08.084 --> 03:10.377
All right. That's good.

03:17.552 --> 03:18.720
My roommate!

03:19.554 --> 03:21.139
Oh. Mr. Park!

03:21.681 --> 03:23.140
Mr. Park.

03:23.141 --> 03:24.934
How have you been?

03:24.935 --> 03:26.353
Sorry, I couldn't call you.

03:28.688 --> 03:30.064
You're here, so it's fine.

03:30.065 --> 03:32.441
Why are you standing out here in the cold?

03:32.442 --> 03:34.193
You didn't know when I'd get here.

03:34.194 --> 03:35.987
I just came out 10 seconds ago.

03:37.697 --> 03:39.866
Goodness. But look at you…

03:40.534 --> 03:44.161
You must have been through a lot.
You look so gaunt.

03:44.162 --> 03:45.788
Do I?

03:45.789 --> 03:47.249
That's awful.

03:47.832 --> 03:49.041
I should get prettier now.

03:50.919 --> 03:52.836
You didn't forget your meds, right?

03:52.837 --> 03:54.673
And your cardiac enzyme levels?

03:55.423 --> 03:57.174
It's cold. Let's go inside.

03:57.175 --> 04:00.427
Genius, Chan is here. Come on in.

04:00.428 --> 04:02.680
- It's cold.
- Are you running away?

04:02.681 --> 04:03.974
Mr. Park!

04:04.641 --> 04:06.976
Genius!

04:06.977 --> 04:08.102
Genius.

04:10.021 --> 04:13.066
Hey, Genius.
Aren't you going to show me your face?

04:13.650 --> 04:14.984
Hey, Grouchy.

04:14.985 --> 04:18.070
You were waiting for Chan the whole time.
Are you protesting?

04:18.071 --> 04:20.156
Leave him.

04:20.657 --> 04:22.784
He's sour because you left
without telling him.

04:23.285 --> 04:24.703
Go upstairs. You must be tired.

04:42.637 --> 04:44.973
Oh… Yes, Mr. Park. Come in.

04:48.643 --> 04:49.644
Oh?

04:51.271 --> 04:53.522
Genius.

04:53.523 --> 04:56.610
Want to sleep with me today?
Hmm?

04:58.320 --> 05:00.655
Dogs should sleep at this hour.

05:01.281 --> 05:02.282
Hmm?

05:02.782 --> 05:03.909
Me?

05:05.410 --> 05:07.579
I have a lot on my mind.

05:08.747 --> 05:13.710
Genius, you know
that Haran should become happy, right?

05:14.961 --> 05:17.839
That's all I wanted for her,

05:19.382 --> 05:20.926
but what do I do now?

05:23.219 --> 05:26.681
I want her to be happy beside me,

05:29.726 --> 05:32.270
and I want her to be happy because of me.

05:33.438 --> 05:35.148
I keep getting greedy.

05:36.316 --> 05:38.484
IF IT'S OKAY WITH YOU, YOU CAN TALK TO ME

05:38.485 --> 05:42.530
The fact that I was fake,
and the reason I became a fake…

05:43.323 --> 05:48.995
The fact that I lived
while he died from that accident…

05:52.832 --> 05:57.420
I keep wanting to do as I want

05:58.546 --> 05:59.965
as if I'm clueless to all that.

06:02.425 --> 06:04.094
Until I go back,

06:05.220 --> 06:08.807
if I play dumb and be greedy,

06:10.016 --> 06:11.267
would that be wrong?

06:17.273 --> 06:19.274
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

06:21.027 --> 06:22.612
Here's today's dress code.

06:23.029 --> 06:25.031
Comfy shoes and warm clothes.

06:25.824 --> 06:26.991
See you later.

06:26.992 --> 06:28.910
I can't travel too far today.

06:30.578 --> 06:31.662
CLOSED DUE TO PERSONAL REASONS

06:31.663 --> 06:32.664
Oh?

06:33.832 --> 06:34.874
Hmm?

06:35.458 --> 06:37.293
Mr. Park…

06:38.378 --> 06:40.045
- Oh! Ms. Song.
- Ms. Song.

06:40.046 --> 06:41.630
- Hey.
- Hello.

06:41.631 --> 06:42.632
What are you all doing…

06:43.299 --> 06:44.883
Ben, when did you get here?

06:44.884 --> 06:45.968
Have you been well?

06:45.969 --> 06:48.512
I visited as soon as I arrived,
and now I'm trapped.

06:49.597 --> 06:52.015
We came when we saw Seunggyu's photo
in our group chat.

06:52.016 --> 06:54.893
I wanted to get the coffee
you bought us last time,

06:54.894 --> 06:57.312
and I saw that Chan was here.

06:57.313 --> 07:01.150
As soon as I saw the photo,
I rushed over with my sheet mask still on.

07:01.151 --> 07:03.569
Things worked out,
so he's staying for two months.

07:03.570 --> 07:04.945
Isn't that great?

07:04.946 --> 07:06.739
Right…

07:06.740 --> 07:07.906
Let's play.

07:07.907 --> 07:09.158
Let's play.

07:09.159 --> 07:11.785
Oh, I gave them to Genius as a gift.

07:11.786 --> 07:15.247
If he presses the buttons,
we can communicate.

07:15.248 --> 07:17.541
I have soccer class,
so I'll be back later.

07:17.542 --> 07:19.668
- Bye.
- Bye.

07:20.837 --> 07:22.463
- Bye.
-  Bye, Donggu.

07:22.464 --> 07:23.547
Bye.

07:23.548 --> 07:25.674
- See you later.
- Ms. Song, sit down.

07:25.675 --> 07:26.842
Right.

07:26.843 --> 07:30.137
We'll need some wine for a welcome party.

07:30.138 --> 07:32.055
Roomie, please get the wine glasses.

07:32.056 --> 07:33.348
Sure.

07:33.349 --> 07:37.019
Mom, I'm going home late today!

07:37.020 --> 07:40.148
Raemee, you live with your mother?
Not alone?

07:55.121 --> 07:56.247
Can I help with anything?

07:57.707 --> 07:59.167
What? Oh…

08:00.460 --> 08:02.754
Ah. It's okay. Sit down.

08:16.976 --> 08:18.519
Please let us clean up.

08:18.520 --> 08:19.728
Please.

08:19.729 --> 08:21.772
The host should clean up.

08:21.773 --> 08:24.316
Just come have some coffee next time.

08:24.317 --> 08:25.484
-  Okay.
-  All right.

08:25.485 --> 08:27.736
-  Then, we'll come have coffee.
-  Okay, thank you.

08:27.737 --> 08:30.030
Thank you.

08:30.031 --> 08:33.909
Still, shouldn't at least one of us
stay back and help clean up?

08:33.910 --> 08:36.119
We're going for another round,

08:36.120 --> 08:38.914
so you can help out here, Lightweight.

08:38.915 --> 08:40.374
- Me?
- Yes, you. Song Haran.

08:40.375 --> 08:41.792
- The lightweight.
- Ah.

08:41.793 --> 08:43.252
Then I'll stay and help too…

08:43.253 --> 08:45.254
Come on. You'll just break the cups.

08:45.255 --> 08:46.922
We'll come back next time. Bye.

08:46.923 --> 08:48.507
- See you next time.
- Okay, bye.

08:48.508 --> 08:50.176
-  I should--
-  Let's go.

08:52.220 --> 08:54.096
My gosh.

08:56.141 --> 08:59.352
I didn't expect them
to all swarm in here.

08:59.853 --> 09:00.854
Yeah.

09:04.858 --> 09:07.359
Sorry. We're going to drink this later.

09:10.321 --> 09:13.616
But it's suddenly so quiet
with all of them gone.

09:14.367 --> 09:16.661
Right. It was pretty noisy in here.

09:17.328 --> 09:18.495
But, Ms. Song--

09:18.496 --> 09:19.788
I love you.

09:25.503 --> 09:28.964
Genius, you shouldn't just
keep pressing those.

09:28.965 --> 09:30.924
What I meant to say is…

09:30.925 --> 09:31.926
I love you.

09:35.555 --> 09:38.807
Has he not been trained yet?

09:38.808 --> 09:40.727
I was trying to say

09:41.227 --> 09:44.354
that I thought you'd be startled
to see everyone here,

09:44.355 --> 09:46.857
so I sent you a message.

09:46.858 --> 09:49.943
Oh. I see.

09:49.944 --> 09:52.613
I'm so full.

09:52.614 --> 09:54.907
I'm going to take a walk with Genius.

09:54.908 --> 09:56.617
You can clean up the rest, right?

09:56.618 --> 09:58.076
Sure. Ms. Song and I--

09:58.077 --> 10:00.120
I love you.

10:00.121 --> 10:01.788
Oops.

10:01.789 --> 10:03.081
My mistake.

10:04.250 --> 10:05.793
See you later. Let's go.

10:10.590 --> 10:13.176
Let's clean this up, then.

10:16.346 --> 10:17.763
You got it on your sleeve.

10:17.764 --> 10:20.099
It'll get stained
if you don't wash it off.

10:28.441 --> 10:29.984
I'll go get changed.

10:35.865 --> 10:38.367
Training on the weekend?

10:38.368 --> 10:39.953
I'm wasting my youth.

10:41.579 --> 10:43.288
Oh? It's Song Hadam.

10:43.289 --> 10:44.832
Oh? It's Cha Yougyum.

10:50.922 --> 10:52.172
Hi.

10:52.173 --> 10:53.674
I'm Kim Seokhyeon from Class 1.

10:53.675 --> 10:55.676
I've been interested in you,

10:55.677 --> 10:58.096
but I don't have to give up
because of Yougyum now.

10:59.180 --> 11:00.472
Can I have your number?

11:00.473 --> 11:02.392
Hey, what is he saying?

11:02.976 --> 11:04.602
Did you two break up?

11:05.103 --> 11:07.729
Cha Yougyum,
are you just going to watch?

11:07.730 --> 11:10.941
If you don't come until I count to three,
I'm giving him my number.

11:10.942 --> 11:13.653
One, two…

11:17.282 --> 11:18.825
All right. I'll give it to you.

11:23.538 --> 11:24.747
Text me.

11:31.212 --> 11:33.171
You got her number.

11:33.172 --> 11:35.590
-  What's this?
-  What?

11:35.591 --> 11:38.427
Please call me if you see her.

11:38.428 --> 11:41.722
If you ever see my mother,
please give me a call.

11:41.723 --> 11:43.182
MISSING ELDERLY WITH DEMENTIA

11:46.769 --> 11:48.021
Kim Nabong.

11:49.105 --> 11:50.606
Hey, Manjae.

11:51.482 --> 11:52.774
Park Genius.

11:52.775 --> 11:55.694
Genius, how have you been?

11:55.695 --> 11:57.279
Were you taking a walk?

11:57.280 --> 11:59.489
Yes, this is a good place to work out.

11:59.490 --> 12:01.908
- I walk a few laps every day.
- No way.

12:01.909 --> 12:04.161
I walk him every day here, too.

12:04.162 --> 12:07.831
Well, I guess we wouldn't have
recognized each other until now.

12:08.916 --> 12:11.335
We can be walking buddies from now on.

12:12.503 --> 12:13.670
Hey.

12:13.671 --> 12:15.213
I think he needs to poop.

12:15.214 --> 12:17.424
He has his own poop area over there.

12:17.425 --> 12:18.967
- Gosh.
- Go and let him poop.

12:18.968 --> 12:21.178
Okay, I'll see you later.

12:21.179 --> 12:23.180
Hey, Genius! Slow down.

12:23.181 --> 12:24.931
All right. Goodness.

12:24.932 --> 12:26.851
Slow down. Okay.

12:33.149 --> 12:36.068
What was she doing here?

12:36.069 --> 12:39.197
- Are you sick or anything?
- I was just visiting a friend there.

12:45.328 --> 12:47.246
MISSING ELDERLY WITH DEMENTIA

12:57.423 --> 12:58.841
Is that you, Yougyum?

13:03.012 --> 13:04.097
Hello.

13:05.223 --> 13:07.057
Why are you wearing glasses?

13:07.058 --> 13:08.809
I almost didn't recognize you.

13:08.810 --> 13:10.519
My eyes are swollen.

13:10.520 --> 13:11.771
How swollen can they be?

13:12.438 --> 13:16.191
My goodness.
They really are incredibly puffy.

13:16.192 --> 13:17.985
How did your eyes get like…

13:19.237 --> 13:20.571
Are you crying?

13:22.782 --> 13:25.409
I had a fight with Hadam,

13:25.410 --> 13:27.829
and it feels like
my whole world just fell apart.

13:29.956 --> 13:33.292
How do I live from now on, Ms. Kim?

13:35.586 --> 13:36.587
Follow me.

13:37.630 --> 13:39.549
What? Where…

13:43.928 --> 13:47.430
Fighting won't make the world fall apart.
It only exhausts you.

13:47.431 --> 13:48.474
Eat up.

13:49.058 --> 13:50.684
I don't have an appetite.

13:50.685 --> 13:54.605
To me, Hadam is my whole world
and my whole universe…

13:55.439 --> 13:57.692
You're out. Just break up with Hadam.

13:58.276 --> 13:59.818
- What?
- I'm not letting a guy

13:59.819 --> 14:02.612
who bawls after one fight
about the world falling apart

14:02.613 --> 14:03.947
date my granddaughter.

14:03.948 --> 14:06.366
How will you survive the big leagues
with that mentality?

14:06.367 --> 14:07.994
You're out.

14:08.578 --> 14:09.871
No…

14:10.621 --> 14:11.789
I'll eat.

14:13.624 --> 14:15.001
Too hot!

14:15.877 --> 14:19.462
I'm only weak when it comes to Hadam.
I push myself hard when I'm training.

14:19.463 --> 14:21.424
I'm the ruthless Cha Yougyum.

14:24.427 --> 14:28.556
Right. At your age, you think the world
falls apart with the smallest things.

14:29.682 --> 14:30.808
I did, too.

14:32.727 --> 14:36.771
But once you go through
something really serious,

14:36.772 --> 14:41.067
you'll realize
that the issues you thought were huge

14:41.068 --> 14:43.320
were actually just tiny specks.

14:43.321 --> 14:47.490
And you'll regret not facing
those issues head-on back then.

14:47.491 --> 14:49.744
You'll think, "Why was I such a coward?"

14:50.870 --> 14:54.497
Anyway, there are dozens of more serious
problems waiting for you in life.

14:54.498 --> 14:56.000
So stop being weak.

14:57.084 --> 14:58.211
Okay.

14:59.462 --> 15:02.798
I'm sorry.
I was absorbed in my own issues.

15:03.507 --> 15:05.050
Ah. What about your checkup?

15:05.051 --> 15:08.470
Something came up at work,
so I rescheduled.

15:08.471 --> 15:10.889
I got scolded
for disappearing from the hospital.

15:17.813 --> 15:20.983
I learned that abalones contain ta…

15:21.817 --> 15:23.068
Ta…

15:23.069 --> 15:24.236
Taurine.

15:24.237 --> 15:26.989
They contain taurine,
which helps with cognitive function.

15:29.075 --> 15:31.494
All right. Give me all the abalones.

15:32.662 --> 15:35.330
I still have a lot to do,
so I have to stay strong.

15:35.331 --> 15:38.792
You eat up, too.
You need the energy to make up with Hadam.

15:38.793 --> 15:40.293
Right. Energy.

15:42.880 --> 15:45.173
Gosh, that's hot.

16:00.022 --> 16:01.606
Mr. Seonu.

16:04.860 --> 16:07.738
Mr. Seonu, there's someone calling you.

16:11.534 --> 16:14.662
Someone keeps calling…

16:15.871 --> 16:17.039
Is he not here?

16:18.874 --> 16:20.543
I'm sorry.

16:21.377 --> 16:22.420
Right.

16:23.170 --> 16:25.422
What is it?

16:25.423 --> 16:26.715
I…

16:28.175 --> 16:30.970
Someone kept calling,
so it seemed important.

16:31.721 --> 16:34.055
- I'm sorry.
- Wait.

16:34.056 --> 16:35.598
Yes?

16:35.599 --> 16:36.600
I mean…

16:46.736 --> 16:50.323
We shouldn't do it here…

16:50.906 --> 16:52.158
- I mean…
- No, I…

16:56.203 --> 16:58.581
- Why are you turning off the lights?
- You…

17:07.006 --> 17:08.883
You're the one who turned them off.

17:11.510 --> 17:12.720
With your back.

17:15.264 --> 17:17.599
Oh. My back…

17:17.600 --> 17:19.142
You've got something on your lips.

17:19.143 --> 17:21.811
Crumbs or something.

17:21.812 --> 17:24.065
It was the crackers…

17:26.150 --> 17:28.401
But why did you close your eyes?

17:31.238 --> 17:34.908
Honestly, anyone would have
misunderstood that situation.

17:34.909 --> 17:38.370
You held my hand and hugged me yesterday,
so I thought…

17:38.371 --> 17:39.497
You thought what?

17:40.581 --> 17:44.043
I just thought you were moving fast
since you're from the States.

17:44.543 --> 17:46.420
This is getting weird.

17:46.921 --> 17:48.630
Stop teasing me.

17:48.631 --> 17:49.923
I wasn't teasing you.

17:49.924 --> 17:52.259
I just thought I saw the old you.

17:52.968 --> 17:54.302
It was cute.

17:54.303 --> 17:55.762
My old self?

17:55.763 --> 17:57.598
What do you mean?

18:00.351 --> 18:02.687
I think I heard you used to be
much more cheerful.

18:03.479 --> 18:04.480
From who?

18:05.398 --> 18:06.649
Was it Hayeong?

18:07.441 --> 18:10.569
Anyway,
I really wasn't teasing you.

18:11.070 --> 18:12.988
I'm sorry.

18:15.241 --> 18:17.910
Ah. I forgot to give you this.

18:19.078 --> 18:20.246
A welcome drink.

18:21.956 --> 18:24.250
I almost took back my word
about being nice to you.

18:26.794 --> 18:28.337
Can we do it now?

18:29.088 --> 18:30.089
Do what?

18:31.006 --> 18:32.882
I meant…

18:32.883 --> 18:34.801
The photos.

18:34.802 --> 18:36.095
Let's check your homework.

18:46.856 --> 18:49.650
You have a talent for this.

18:50.276 --> 18:52.403
Oh, my gosh.

18:55.239 --> 18:57.491
You liar.
You said there were just 10 shots.

18:59.994 --> 19:03.413
Hmm? My Destinations List…

19:03.414 --> 19:06.167
It's yours. I took a photo of it.

19:07.168 --> 19:09.670
- When did you take this?
- What?

19:10.212 --> 19:11.421
This!

19:11.422 --> 19:15.925
I just took this for fun
when I was bored…

19:15.926 --> 19:17.928
Wow. That's not fair.

19:18.596 --> 19:20.139
You promised to do that with me.

19:21.140 --> 19:22.891
That doesn't count. I'm confiscating this.

19:22.892 --> 19:24.726
Everything you did alone is invalid.

19:24.727 --> 19:26.770
We'll do everything together.

19:26.771 --> 19:28.689
Geez.

19:30.149 --> 19:33.860
But what's that last thing
you scribbled out?

19:33.861 --> 19:36.739
Mmm.

19:37.406 --> 19:40.868
I thought it would be impossible,
so I scribbled it out…

19:44.997 --> 19:46.332
but it might be possible now.

19:47.917 --> 19:49.251
It's a secret, though.

19:52.755 --> 19:55.298
Why did you tell me
to wear comfy shoes today?

19:55.299 --> 19:58.676
I thought we'd just walk around a bit

19:58.677 --> 20:00.553
without any specific plans.

20:00.554 --> 20:02.388
Just go wherever the wind takes us?

20:03.766 --> 20:05.976
I wanted to try that with you.

20:06.602 --> 20:08.144
Go somewhere and try things

20:08.145 --> 20:11.440
without thinking of what happens next.

20:12.608 --> 20:13.651
No,

20:14.610 --> 20:16.737
that may have messed things up.

20:17.530 --> 20:21.200
If things get messed up, we can fix them.
It's the same for knots.

20:22.034 --> 20:24.912
Sometimes they seem impossible to undo,

20:25.412 --> 20:28.707
but if you loosen one strand at a time,
they'll unravel.

20:30.042 --> 20:32.962
You can find a way,
no matter how impossible it seems.

20:36.048 --> 20:37.550
Shall we do it tomorrow?

20:38.300 --> 20:41.095
Try going wherever the wind takes us.

20:41.887 --> 20:43.388
Sorry. Next time.

20:43.389 --> 20:46.558
I have to go somewhere far
with my family tomorrow.

20:46.559 --> 20:48.018
Far? Where?

20:51.564 --> 20:52.565
Ah.

20:53.482 --> 20:54.899
THE LATE SONG JUNHO
THE LATE MIN HYEWON

20:54.900 --> 20:58.195
Dad's favorite crab stew.

21:00.614 --> 21:03.908
Remember when Dad chipped his tooth
eating crab stew?

21:03.909 --> 21:06.829
Right, he visited the dentist
for a long time after that.

21:08.205 --> 21:09.873
Hadam, wait.

21:09.874 --> 21:12.585
Put the castella on Mom's favorite dish.

21:13.377 --> 21:17.046
Wow. That's a real antique.
We've had that since I was a baby.

21:17.047 --> 21:19.924
Whenever we were in a bad mood,
she gave us snacks on this.

21:19.925 --> 21:21.676
Mom always said,

21:21.677 --> 21:25.638
"When you're feeling down,
having sweets on a pretty dish

21:25.639 --> 21:27.891
- will make you feel sparkly."
- Sparkly.

21:35.149 --> 21:36.817
-  Let's greet them now.
-  Okay.

21:41.447 --> 21:45.159
This might be
my last time coming here.

21:46.785 --> 21:48.077
If, by any chance,

21:48.078 --> 21:51.373
I start acting too strange,
just call me home to you quickly.

21:51.957 --> 21:54.960
I don't want to embarrass myself
in front of them.

21:55.628 --> 21:56.754
Okay, Hyewon?

21:57.671 --> 21:58.881
Okay, Junho?

22:06.889 --> 22:09.891
I will take you all home safely.

22:09.892 --> 22:11.101
Let's go.

22:13.896 --> 22:18.816
Ah…
My bad feelings are never wrong.

22:18.817 --> 22:19.818
I forgot my phone.

22:21.362 --> 22:23.738
- I'm riding with Haran.
- Eh?

22:23.739 --> 22:26.450
You're really going to betray me? Hey!

22:28.994 --> 22:30.746
She's so cold.

22:31.956 --> 22:34.500
♪ I dream a little bit of red alone ♪

22:41.298 --> 22:42.799
No, I had it then.

22:42.800 --> 22:44.092
And then, Grandma…

22:44.093 --> 22:47.388
I greeted Mom and Dad,
then I got up, and my phone…

22:47.846 --> 22:49.348
Where did I leave it?

22:50.849 --> 22:52.016
-  I'm really sorry.
- Eh?

22:52.017 --> 22:53.101
Who's that?

22:53.102 --> 22:54.352
I'm sorry.

22:54.353 --> 22:57.021
Excuse me, that's my parents' grave.

22:57.022 --> 22:58.816
I think you came to the wrong…

23:00.859 --> 23:02.069
Mr. Yeon?

23:02.695 --> 23:03.988
Why are you…

23:05.114 --> 23:06.197
Are you crying?

23:06.198 --> 23:08.324
Oh… No.

23:08.325 --> 23:10.744
You are. Your eyes are red.

23:11.286 --> 23:13.372
People would think
you're their son…

23:17.668 --> 23:18.794
Thank you.

23:19.878 --> 23:21.504
How pretty.

23:21.505 --> 23:24.215
You don't need to do this
for Parents' Day.

23:24.216 --> 23:27.427
You always welcome me
and pack me side dishes.

23:27.428 --> 23:30.430
I'm a bit awkward
with expressing my feelings,

23:30.431 --> 23:32.890
but I really wanted to thank you today.

23:34.393 --> 23:35.977
Goodness. Thank you.

23:35.978 --> 23:37.895
My friends brag about their sons.

23:37.896 --> 23:40.690
I can brag to them that I got
carnations from my son, too.

23:41.817 --> 23:45.361
Since we're all dressed up,
how about a family photo?

23:45.362 --> 23:46.904
That sounds great.

23:46.905 --> 23:48.781
- Let's take a photo over there.
- Okay.

23:48.782 --> 23:51.784
- Oh, sure.
-  Let's take a photo.

23:51.785 --> 23:53.786
- All right.
-  Mr. Yeon.

23:53.787 --> 23:56.080
- Let's take it together.
- Come on, Mr. Yeon.

23:56.081 --> 23:57.707
- Join us.
- Come here.

23:57.708 --> 23:59.208
It's okay.

23:59.209 --> 24:01.210
It's a family photo. Come here.

24:01.211 --> 24:04.048
Sir, can you take a photo of us?

24:05.591 --> 24:06.799
All right.

24:06.800 --> 24:08.384
One, two, three.

24:18.353 --> 24:19.896
Mom, Dad.

24:19.897 --> 24:22.899
Our former chauffeur, Mr. Yeon,
became our COO.

24:22.900 --> 24:27.029
He's a core figure now,
like me in our household.

24:27.613 --> 24:30.157
So send him lots of energy.

24:34.078 --> 24:35.788
Thank you for taking care

24:37.039 --> 24:38.582
of our parents, too.

24:41.543 --> 24:42.544
I'm sorry.

24:43.003 --> 24:45.713
Why do you keep saying sorry?

24:45.714 --> 24:46.715
I…

24:48.509 --> 24:50.135
I'm really sorry.

24:53.680 --> 24:56.849
Oh. I dropped my phone somewhere.

24:56.850 --> 24:58.310
Can you call my number?

25:01.939 --> 25:04.107
Where is it?

25:04.108 --> 25:06.026
I hear it. Where is it?

25:07.236 --> 25:09.071
Is it here? Is it here?

25:09.655 --> 25:10.738
Is it here?

25:10.739 --> 25:11.740
I…

25:12.908 --> 25:14.409
It's coming from your butt.

25:15.119 --> 25:16.954
My butt?

25:17.579 --> 25:21.125
Darn it. I came all the way
back up here for nothing.

25:21.875 --> 25:24.878
Since we met here,

25:25.671 --> 25:26.922
should we go eat something?

25:27.339 --> 25:28.422
Eat?

25:28.423 --> 25:30.675
I promised you I'd treat you last time.

25:30.676 --> 25:34.221
It was 39,000 won last time,

25:35.806 --> 25:38.599
so I'll treat you to up to 80,000 won.

25:38.600 --> 25:41.644
There's an amazing
oxtail soup place nearby.

25:41.645 --> 25:42.728
What do you say?

25:42.729 --> 25:43.980
Let's go!

25:43.981 --> 25:45.940
It's okay…

25:45.941 --> 25:47.484
No, it's not okay.

25:48.110 --> 25:50.027
Have we eaten together before?

25:50.028 --> 25:52.155
Who do you normally
have lunch with at work?

25:52.156 --> 25:54.782
What do you usually do on the weekend?

25:54.783 --> 25:55.950
Wait.

26:00.247 --> 26:01.330
Your hand.

26:01.331 --> 26:03.458
You might slip
since you're wearing heels.

26:07.588 --> 26:09.047
It's fine, I can wipe them.

26:09.715 --> 26:10.716
Be careful.

26:19.308 --> 26:21.643
You really are considerate.

26:22.352 --> 26:24.605
You always look out for our family.

26:28.066 --> 26:30.027
Why did he cry, though?

26:37.451 --> 26:39.077
How was your visit to your parents?

26:39.578 --> 26:40.912
Hey.

26:40.913 --> 26:43.332
Whose message
is making you smile like that?

26:43.957 --> 26:45.333
What?

26:45.334 --> 26:48.127
What took you so long?
Weren't you looking for your phone?

26:48.128 --> 26:50.047
I was hungry, so I got some oxtail soup.

26:50.672 --> 26:52.298
I'm so full.

26:52.299 --> 26:53.674
That's good.

26:53.675 --> 26:55.052
Hey, Hayeong.

26:55.844 --> 27:00.097
Did you ever tell Mr. Seonu about my past?

27:00.098 --> 27:03.142
Like how I was different before
or something like that?

27:03.143 --> 27:06.646
Like how you used to be
really bubbly and friendly?

27:06.647 --> 27:08.105
Something like that.

27:08.106 --> 27:09.650
Mmm? No, I didn't…

27:11.109 --> 27:12.986
Wait, did I?

27:13.820 --> 27:16.155
I'm 29 now.

27:16.156 --> 27:17.366
My memory isn't so good…

27:18.700 --> 27:21.954
- But why do you ask?
- He spoke as if he knew me.

27:22.412 --> 27:23.413
Really?

27:24.581 --> 27:27.708
But are you two really close?

27:27.709 --> 27:29.919
Mr. Seonu, Ms. Song…

27:29.920 --> 27:31.046
You're so formal.

27:31.880 --> 27:33.923
Then what should I call him?

27:33.924 --> 27:35.591
You're the same age.

27:35.592 --> 27:37.301
Use your first names.

27:37.302 --> 27:39.972
You can just say, "Hey, Haran. Hey, Chan…"

27:42.557 --> 27:43.808
I should go shower.

27:43.809 --> 27:45.185
Why did you suddenly stop?

27:46.019 --> 27:47.104
Well…

27:48.230 --> 27:50.440
You used to call him Chan.

27:51.233 --> 27:54.528
Your old boyfriend, Hyeokchan.

27:55.821 --> 27:57.990
I just realized their names were similar.

27:58.865 --> 28:00.324
Oh…

28:00.325 --> 28:02.952
Right. I didn't think about that.

28:07.457 --> 28:09.250
Make…

28:09.251 --> 28:12.879
MAKE HER HAPPY AGAIN, NO MATTER WHAT!

28:14.881 --> 28:17.551
Their names… were similar.

28:18.343 --> 28:19.594
All right…

28:28.937 --> 28:30.397
What was that?

28:30.897 --> 28:33.775
EMPTY SPOT IN MEMORY - FOURTH

28:34.943 --> 28:37.112
A waste container…

28:37.988 --> 28:39.072
and that sound again.

28:41.116 --> 28:42.616
The lab…

28:42.617 --> 28:44.201
The sound of metal…

28:44.202 --> 28:45.536
The explosion.

28:45.537 --> 28:49.207
The missing gap
started with that sound, too.

28:52.878 --> 28:54.713
And the second memory

28:55.338 --> 28:56.548
had that sound as well.

28:59.926 --> 29:03.889
And the third memory
had the same sound.

29:05.348 --> 29:07.184
Why did those missing memories

29:07.976 --> 29:10.227
start with the sound of her bracelet?

29:10.228 --> 29:12.229
Sorry, Ran.
My professor's calling.

29:12.230 --> 29:13.397
I'll call you back later.

29:13.398 --> 29:14.733
Hey, Sujin. You're here?

29:15.233 --> 29:18.904
Why are they all connected to this person?

29:22.574 --> 29:25.368
SUJIN?

29:26.286 --> 29:27.829
Sujin?

29:44.763 --> 29:46.430
This is Cha Sujin.

29:46.431 --> 29:48.099
I've arrived in Korea.

29:48.100 --> 29:50.102
I'll head to the hospital straight away.

29:56.900 --> 29:59.152
It's my fault for causing
the misunderstanding.

29:59.861 --> 30:01.029
I'm sorry.

30:02.447 --> 30:03.865
I'm sorry about everything.

30:09.371 --> 30:10.872
I'm sorry about everything.

30:11.498 --> 30:12.874
I'm sorry about everything…

30:19.131 --> 30:21.424
I'll give it to you. Text me.

30:45.157 --> 30:46.158
Cha Yougyum?

30:48.076 --> 30:50.244
Hey, what are you doing here?

31:09.848 --> 31:11.600
What are you doing? Give it.

31:26.448 --> 31:27.657
Are you okay?

31:28.491 --> 31:29.867
Oh?

31:29.868 --> 31:30.951
That's Mom's dish.

31:30.952 --> 31:32.536
Song Hadam.

31:32.537 --> 31:34.121
Don't you know we never use that?

31:34.122 --> 31:35.998
There are dozens of dishes. Why did you--

31:35.999 --> 31:38.500
Then why are you making a fuss
over one dish?

31:38.501 --> 31:41.086
Hey. Why are you talking like that?

31:41.087 --> 31:43.047
Don't you know what that dish is?

31:43.048 --> 31:44.257
- It's Mom's--
- I don't!

31:45.008 --> 31:46.133
I don't know.

31:46.134 --> 31:47.927
I'm the only one who doesn't know.

31:47.928 --> 31:50.638
I can hardly even remember
Mom and Dad's voices or faces,

31:50.639 --> 31:53.474
so how would I know
how special that stupid dish is?

31:53.475 --> 31:55.726
I want to remember, too.

31:55.727 --> 31:57.687
I want to miss them too,

31:58.355 --> 32:00.440
but I can't remember.

32:02.484 --> 32:07.280
Whenever you talk about Mom and Dad,
I feel like I don't belong.

32:08.114 --> 32:10.867
I feel like I'm the only one
who wasn't their daughter.

32:12.369 --> 32:14.996
- Hey…
- I was only six.

32:15.622 --> 32:16.831
I…

32:18.124 --> 32:19.667
I didn't know anything…

32:21.253 --> 32:22.254
Hadam.

32:22.963 --> 32:24.088
We're sorry.

32:24.089 --> 32:25.674
I'm sorry, Hadam.

32:30.720 --> 32:31.930
I'm going to school.

32:32.847 --> 32:34.224
I'm really sorry…

32:36.893 --> 32:38.103
I broke Mom's dish.

32:49.906 --> 32:53.326
You said you have a meeting.
Go get ready. I'll clean this.

32:55.829 --> 32:56.913
Okay, thanks.

32:57.539 --> 32:59.541
We'll talk to Hadam when she comes home.

33:11.344 --> 33:12.470
Hey, Hadam.

33:15.640 --> 33:17.684
Let me see your hand. Where is it?

33:18.685 --> 33:19.936
Gosh.

33:26.067 --> 33:28.277
I just got this at a convenience store.

33:28.278 --> 33:29.653
It's just a temporary fix,

33:29.654 --> 33:32.991
so go to the nurse's office, okay?

33:34.117 --> 33:36.578
But what do we do

33:37.579 --> 33:38.788
about Mom's dish?

33:39.372 --> 33:41.206
That dish isn't the problem.

33:41.207 --> 33:43.209
You hurt your hand
when the CSAT is coming up.

33:43.877 --> 33:45.503
I'm ambidextrous.

33:46.755 --> 33:48.839
You are? Since when?

33:48.840 --> 33:50.716
I practiced using my left hand

33:50.717 --> 33:52.843
because my hand hurt
when I studied too long.

33:52.844 --> 33:54.387
But I was a natural at it.

33:55.055 --> 33:56.306
Our baby sister.

33:57.057 --> 33:58.350
You take after Mom.

33:59.976 --> 34:00.977
Mom?

34:02.062 --> 34:03.646
Mom was ambidextrous.

34:04.522 --> 34:06.648
We wondered
where her genes went.

34:06.649 --> 34:08.568
I guess they all went to you.

34:10.987 --> 34:14.991
Did you want to find out
what she meant by feeling sparkly?

34:15.992 --> 34:17.285
Is that why you took it out?

34:17.911 --> 34:18.994
Huh?

34:18.995 --> 34:23.541
Didn't you want to eat sweets from it
and feel better?

34:27.420 --> 34:28.629
Hadam.

34:28.630 --> 34:31.341
Let's talk more about Mom and Dad
from now on.

34:32.550 --> 34:37.221
I was actually worried
we'd forget about them when time passed.

34:37.222 --> 34:40.891
But I guess we can tell
our smart baby sister about them

34:40.892 --> 34:42.310
as a backup file.

34:43.478 --> 34:46.480
I do have a good memory.

34:47.857 --> 34:51.194
How long are you going to follow me?

34:52.654 --> 34:55.865
I'm escorting you properly today,

34:56.324 --> 34:57.492
all the way to school.

34:58.618 --> 35:03.206
Aren't you the least bit aware
of your current condition?

35:04.416 --> 35:06.918
- Are you embarrassed of me?
- A bit.

35:07.711 --> 35:08.961
Hadam!

35:08.962 --> 35:10.546
Oh? It's Yeongju.

35:10.547 --> 35:11.839
Bye.

35:11.840 --> 35:12.966
Jeong Yeongju!

35:13.758 --> 35:15.427
Go to the nurse's office!

35:16.511 --> 35:18.930
You'll catch a cold. Go home.

35:20.014 --> 35:21.641
Bye!

35:34.529 --> 35:36.948
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

35:39.451 --> 35:42.369
Let's go on a walk.

35:42.370 --> 35:44.538
-  Genius.
-  Let's go on a walk.

35:44.539 --> 35:46.498
You seem to be abusing that.

35:46.499 --> 35:50.794
And you're such a chatterbox.

35:50.795 --> 35:52.005
Watch your mouth, okay?

35:53.465 --> 35:56.050
-  Let's play.
- Okay.

35:56.676 --> 35:57.760
Let's go on a walk.

35:57.761 --> 35:59.970
Mr. Park, I'll go on a run with Genius.

35:59.971 --> 36:01.430
Don't you have a meeting?

36:01.431 --> 36:02.848
I still have some time.

36:02.849 --> 36:04.141
Right.

36:04.142 --> 36:07.436
Something arrived from the US
while you were away.

36:07.437 --> 36:10.147
I forgot about it.
It's in the counter cabinet.

36:10.148 --> 36:11.149
Ah.

36:28.041 --> 36:29.042
Mmm?

36:33.630 --> 36:34.631
Hello?

36:36.090 --> 36:37.592
What was that message?

36:38.176 --> 36:39.761
Why is it a secret from Ms. Song?

36:42.430 --> 36:43.431
Ah.

36:44.140 --> 36:46.643
Okay, I'll keep it a secret. All right.

36:49.020 --> 36:50.646
What did you receive?

36:50.647 --> 36:53.398
It's nothing special.

36:55.652 --> 36:57.903
I'll clean up. Go. He's so eager to leave.

36:59.280 --> 37:01.115
- Genius, let's go. Come on.
- Go on.

37:01.991 --> 37:03.951
Let's go, Genius.

37:03.952 --> 37:05.161
Let's run!

37:15.755 --> 37:16.756
What is this?

37:17.340 --> 37:20.260
"Newbury Street, Boston…"

37:21.094 --> 37:22.720
What was the package?

37:23.763 --> 37:25.180
-  Hello, Mr. Park.
- Oh!

37:25.181 --> 37:27.308
-  Hello.
- Welcome. Come in.

37:32.188 --> 37:34.940
You mean there will be
more parts on Korea?

37:34.941 --> 37:38.569
Yes, the interim feedback
was really positive.

37:38.570 --> 37:41.405
The response to Won's outfit
was incredible.

37:41.406 --> 37:46.076
The cloud motif, Korean color palette,
dancheong, and the hanbok panel.

37:46.077 --> 37:51.248
Wow. Everyone was impressed
by the details that represented Korea.

37:51.249 --> 37:56.254
The most Korean things
are what end up being popular worldwide!

37:56.838 --> 38:01.384
So we'd like to request another outfit
once we get the revised script,

38:02.218 --> 38:04.469
if that's okay with you…

38:04.470 --> 38:07.140
Don't be silly. Of course, that's okay.

38:07.932 --> 38:10.310
If it will help with the project,
anything's fine.

38:12.270 --> 38:13.688
- Thank you.
-  Thank you.

38:14.230 --> 38:16.565
Right. We just have to push
straight ahead now.

38:16.566 --> 38:18.692
Let's pick up the pace again.

38:18.693 --> 38:20.527
How about a round of applause?

38:20.528 --> 38:23.030
Everybody, clap!

38:32.624 --> 38:35.293
Plans? Is it about work?

38:36.210 --> 38:37.377
Mmm…

38:37.378 --> 38:39.213
I think it's a secret.

38:46.512 --> 38:49.349
There should at least be
one pen that you like.

38:51.434 --> 38:53.603
I guess she didn't find
any that she liked.

38:54.103 --> 38:55.187
What?

38:55.188 --> 38:56.313
It's nothing.

38:57.607 --> 38:58.983
Bye, then.

39:00.485 --> 39:01.611
Bye.

39:03.196 --> 39:04.656
See you later. I'll text you.

39:09.452 --> 39:11.996
Who is he meeting, though?

39:12.789 --> 39:15.707
Then are your parents
in LA as well?

39:17.001 --> 39:19.545
Oh… No.

39:20.088 --> 39:22.339
My mother passed away when I was nine.

39:22.340 --> 39:26.385
My father's probably teaching in Daejeon.

39:26.386 --> 39:27.929
We don't really keep in touch.

39:28.972 --> 39:29.973
Well…

39:30.473 --> 39:34.769
Every family has its own issues.

39:35.645 --> 39:37.312
Go on and eat.

39:37.313 --> 39:38.772
Thank you.

39:38.773 --> 39:40.023
Right.

39:40.024 --> 39:43.193
Will you stay in LA again
once the collaboration is over?

39:44.362 --> 39:47.115
Yes, I believe so. But why do you ask?

39:48.199 --> 39:50.660
Should I establish a branch in LA
and send her there?

39:51.703 --> 39:52.953
Excuse me?

39:52.954 --> 39:55.580
Ah. I was just talking to myself.

39:55.581 --> 39:59.292
But why aren't you eating? Hmm?

39:59.293 --> 40:02.796
I wanted to treat you to something
after all that trouble at headquarters.

40:02.797 --> 40:03.922
Eat up.

40:03.923 --> 40:07.884
Why did you only ask for me?
Ben went through a lot, too.

40:07.885 --> 40:09.887
- Who?
- You know, with the…

40:10.471 --> 40:13.724
Oh… Producer Ben?

40:13.725 --> 40:15.142
Well,

40:15.143 --> 40:18.311
I'm sure his in-laws
will take good care of him.

40:18.312 --> 40:21.606
Just think of this as a meal
from your in-laws.

40:21.607 --> 40:23.901
In-laws?

40:24.777 --> 40:28.113
I'm just saying…

40:28.114 --> 40:30.158
Darn it. I can't do this.

40:32.160 --> 40:33.452
I'm sorry.

40:33.453 --> 40:36.038
Beating around the bush
isn't really my style,

40:36.039 --> 40:37.622
so let me be blunt.

40:37.623 --> 40:39.333
Oh. Sure, be blunt…

40:39.959 --> 40:41.836
I mean, feel free to say what you want.

40:43.546 --> 40:46.591
How much do you know about Haran's past?

40:47.592 --> 40:48.885
Quite a lot.

40:50.344 --> 40:52.805
Did you hear about her losing her parents?

40:54.348 --> 40:55.432
I heard.

40:55.433 --> 40:58.644
And losing her boyfriend seven years ago?

41:02.065 --> 41:03.441
I know that, too.

41:06.778 --> 41:08.154
Even after losing her parents,

41:09.155 --> 41:11.574
she stayed strong,

41:12.492 --> 41:15.661
but that incident left Haran
trapped in winter,

41:16.537 --> 41:18.748
just like you said.

41:20.625 --> 41:22.167
Haran's not eating.

41:22.168 --> 41:23.585
Again?

41:23.586 --> 41:26.922
She's not eating or sleeping.

41:26.923 --> 41:28.424
She'll die at this rate, Grandma.

41:29.884 --> 41:32.803
She no longer smiled
or showed any expressions…

41:32.804 --> 41:35.597
- Eat a sausage, Hadam.
- …even in front of her sisters,

41:35.598 --> 41:38.100
and even in front of me,
when we used to be like friends.

41:38.101 --> 41:39.893
Just don't go.

41:39.894 --> 41:42.354
What if something happens to you outside?

41:42.355 --> 41:45.399
It happened to Mom and Dad.
So don't go, okay?

41:46.317 --> 41:49.694
It's okay.
Haran, it's all right. It's okay.

41:49.695 --> 41:52.115
If I let her stay buried
in all that anxiety,

41:52.698 --> 41:54.367
I felt like I would lose her.

41:59.247 --> 42:00.455
Come out.

42:00.456 --> 42:01.457
I'm not eating.

42:02.542 --> 42:04.000
Just leave me alone.

42:04.001 --> 42:05.669
Get up. Right now.

42:05.670 --> 42:09.674
I knew I had to do whatever I could
to pull her out.

42:10.675 --> 42:12.300
You're working here from now on.

42:12.301 --> 42:14.469
I'll give you a month
to organize the storage room.

42:14.470 --> 42:16.556
Why are you doing this?

42:17.265 --> 42:19.267
I don't want to. I'm leaving.

42:19.892 --> 42:20.976
That's an order.

42:20.977 --> 42:23.354
If you want to keep sleeping
under my roof,

42:23.980 --> 42:25.106
do as I say.

42:25.940 --> 42:29.484
I had to grow cold,
and I had to stay strong.

42:29.485 --> 42:32.864
I had to save her first.

43:12.361 --> 43:13.654
Come out.

43:18.868 --> 43:21.244
She could hardly move an inch,

43:21.245 --> 43:24.623
but she finally started moving
little by little,

43:24.624 --> 43:26.292
and her eyes started shining.

43:37.553 --> 43:40.640
She was living again,
little by little.

43:50.149 --> 43:51.692
She's alive now.

44:02.703 --> 44:04.956
Come to work on the third floor
starting tomorrow.

44:05.790 --> 44:10.503
You'll be the rookie assistant
for Design Team 1, 2, and 3.

44:12.922 --> 44:16.258
I was relieved at the fact
that she held on once more

44:16.259 --> 44:18.134
without crumbling down.

44:18.135 --> 44:20.845
But then, she changed.

44:20.846 --> 44:23.723
- This is an apology for taking a leave.
-  Thank you.

44:23.724 --> 44:25.643
She started smiling again recently.

44:26.727 --> 44:29.604
I know I met a great person.

44:29.605 --> 44:31.357
I feel grateful.

44:32.358 --> 44:33.985
She learned how to cry again, too.

44:38.739 --> 44:39.865
Mr. Seonu.

44:42.285 --> 44:43.536
Why would you…

44:43.995 --> 44:44.996
Thank you.

44:45.663 --> 44:47.914
I wanted to speak to you today

44:47.915 --> 44:50.334
as Haran's grandmother,
not the head of the atelier.

44:51.294 --> 44:54.963
Thank you so much for letting me see Haran

44:54.964 --> 44:58.134
crying and laughing again.

44:59.593 --> 45:01.304
No, I…

45:02.054 --> 45:03.221
I didn't do anything…

45:03.222 --> 45:05.056
They say that if it's fate,

45:05.057 --> 45:07.517
you'll meet
no matter how far apart you are.

45:07.518 --> 45:08.935
You came all the way here.

45:08.936 --> 45:11.313
I don't think
you were meant to just work here.

45:12.732 --> 45:13.774
Thanks to you,

45:14.692 --> 45:16.277
I'll be able to leave in peace.

45:17.945 --> 45:19.405
Are you going somewhere?

45:20.406 --> 45:21.407
Well,

45:22.825 --> 45:26.453
I'm planning to stay in France
after I retire.

45:26.454 --> 45:28.163
If you stay by Haran's side,

45:28.164 --> 45:31.166
I won't be that worried about her.

45:31.167 --> 45:32.877
Ah.

45:34.879 --> 45:38.090
But, Ms. Kim,

45:39.342 --> 45:42.053
I may not be as good for her

45:43.554 --> 45:47.183
as you believe.

45:54.815 --> 45:57.526
My heart is throbbing,

45:58.736 --> 46:00.446
and tears keep flowing.

46:01.197 --> 46:02.198
My heart

46:03.366 --> 46:05.034
hurts more than my foot.

46:06.160 --> 46:07.952
Do you think it's serious?

46:07.953 --> 46:11.498
Cut the drama and go to a bigger hospital.

46:11.499 --> 46:13.166
I can't treat that properly here.

46:13.167 --> 46:15.711
I'm sure it's just because
I trained hard these days.

46:16.253 --> 46:17.962
Just give me something for the bruise.

46:25.554 --> 46:26.971
Can you move aside?

46:26.972 --> 46:28.723
Huh? Oh…

46:38.901 --> 46:40.318
Can I help you with anything?

46:40.319 --> 46:42.780
Why did Yougyum come here?

46:43.364 --> 46:44.697
Is he hurt?

46:44.698 --> 46:45.990
That's personal information.

46:48.702 --> 46:51.497
Is she sick or something?

46:54.125 --> 46:56.419
She has to stay healthy.

47:03.008 --> 47:05.051
Mmm.

47:05.052 --> 47:06.845
Hey, you came back.

47:06.846 --> 47:11.225
I finished my first appointment,
so I'm here for the next one with you.

47:13.769 --> 47:16.438
Seriously, what are we doing here?

47:16.439 --> 47:17.440
You'll see.

47:18.524 --> 47:21.610
KIM SEON POTTERY EXHIBITION

47:22.361 --> 47:23.821
Pottery exhibition?

47:25.072 --> 47:26.281
No way.

47:26.282 --> 47:28.242
-  Oh. You're here.
- Grandma!

47:30.244 --> 47:33.037
Goodness.

47:33.038 --> 47:35.081
-  I missed you.
- I feel neglected lately.

47:35.082 --> 47:36.291
-  How are you?
- It's okay.

47:36.292 --> 47:37.293
Have you been well?

47:37.960 --> 47:40.170
You should have told me
we were seeing her.

47:40.171 --> 47:42.006
It's not my fault. She told me not to.

47:42.882 --> 47:44.841
If I'd known, I would've gotten flowers--

47:44.842 --> 47:47.051
That's why I told him to keep it secret.

47:47.052 --> 47:51.140
And why would I need flowers
when such a precious guest is here?

47:51.891 --> 47:53.100
Are you two dating?

47:53.809 --> 47:55.310
You little brat.

47:55.311 --> 47:57.937
You should've told me
you were going to the States.

47:57.938 --> 48:00.732
- I was worried when I couldn't reach you.
- I told you.

48:00.733 --> 48:03.443
- I suddenly had to go--
- Still, you should have told her.

48:03.444 --> 48:04.527
Right?

48:04.528 --> 48:06.321
Wow. You're teaming up on me?

48:06.322 --> 48:07.822
That's so mean. I'm leaving.

48:07.823 --> 48:10.825
Come and look around.
And get the cup you made last time.

48:10.826 --> 48:12.827
It looks so beautiful.

48:12.828 --> 48:16.080
Really? I'm so excited.

48:16.081 --> 48:17.999
My hands look pretty, don't they?

48:18.000 --> 48:20.293
No one's coming for me?

48:20.294 --> 48:21.712
I want to be doted on, too!

48:35.684 --> 48:37.685
Oh. This one looks a bit different.

48:37.686 --> 48:41.314
The lines seem pretty rough,
but it's so cool.

48:41.315 --> 48:44.193
The lines are where I mended them.

48:44.777 --> 48:47.613
I put together the shattered pieces.

48:48.113 --> 48:50.031
You can put shattered pieces together?

48:50.032 --> 48:51.491
You know lacquer trees, right?

48:51.492 --> 48:53.786
The sap acts as a natural adhesive.

48:54.370 --> 48:57.789
Once I attach the pieces
and let them dry carefully…

48:57.790 --> 49:01.168
Then they become a new art piece.

49:03.003 --> 49:07.132
They shatter, get hurt, then heal,

49:07.758 --> 49:09.635
and in the process, they gain depth.

49:10.886 --> 49:13.097
It's similar to people, right?

49:16.559 --> 49:20.728
Oh… Would it be possible
to restore a broken plate?

49:20.729 --> 49:24.232
It's a dish my mom treasured,
but they don't sell it anymore.

49:24.233 --> 49:27.486
Bring it over sometime.
I'll do my best to restore it.

49:27.945 --> 49:29.696
Ms. Kim.

49:29.697 --> 49:32.074
You're here. Hang on.

49:32.658 --> 49:33.992
Look around.

49:36.662 --> 49:38.663
We shouldn't meet like this anymore.

49:38.664 --> 49:39.956
I just get lonely.

49:41.250 --> 49:44.627
Shouldn't you go and greet them?
They seem like her friends.

49:44.628 --> 49:46.546
Chan, come and say hi.

49:46.547 --> 49:48.006
Okay.

49:48.007 --> 49:49.508
I'll be back soon.

49:52.469 --> 49:55.638
Oh. The kid who visited during vacation?

49:55.639 --> 49:58.808
- Yes.
- You've gotten so handsome!

49:58.809 --> 50:01.561
Thank you.
I turned out pretty well, didn't I?

50:01.562 --> 50:04.230
Oh my. Look how cheeky he's gotten.

50:05.733 --> 50:07.525
You used to call him Chan.

50:07.526 --> 50:10.362
Your old boyfriend, Hyeokchan.

50:11.113 --> 50:12.489
Seonu Chan?

50:14.450 --> 50:15.576
Seonu…

50:16.410 --> 50:17.453
Chan.

50:21.999 --> 50:23.541
He's shameless, like me.

50:31.091 --> 50:33.176
Oh? There's no one here.

50:33.177 --> 50:34.802
Everyone went home.

50:34.803 --> 50:36.304
Is Hayeong not here?

50:36.305 --> 50:38.723
We were going to discuss
the new material today.

50:38.724 --> 50:41.517
She was feeble all day,
unlike her usual self,

50:41.518 --> 50:42.977
and went home early.

50:42.978 --> 50:44.479
Try calling her.

50:44.480 --> 50:45.481
Bye, then.

50:52.363 --> 50:54.113
Ms. Song.

50:54.114 --> 50:55.281
Hello?

50:55.282 --> 50:57.034
Are you a friend of hers?

50:58.243 --> 51:01.120
She's been drinking and sleeping nonstop.

51:01.121 --> 51:02.873
You should come and take her home.

51:15.886 --> 51:16.887
Ah.

51:17.513 --> 51:19.598
Good morning.

51:20.182 --> 51:21.766
When did I come to work, though?

51:21.767 --> 51:24.018
You got off work. This is a wine bar.

51:24.019 --> 51:25.603
I'll take you home.

51:25.604 --> 51:28.564
What? To where? Home?

51:28.565 --> 51:30.693
No, I can't.

51:31.694 --> 51:33.862
I can't face Hadam.

51:36.615 --> 51:40.202
I should have told her more
about Mom and Dad.

51:41.161 --> 51:43.497
I should have known how she felt.

51:44.540 --> 51:47.000
I should have known

51:47.793 --> 51:49.837
so no one would get hurt.

51:51.588 --> 51:55.341
Hadam was only six at the time.

51:55.342 --> 51:59.263
But she was in the car with Mom and Dad

52:00.055 --> 52:01.473
during…

52:02.349 --> 52:04.143
the accident…

52:17.740 --> 52:18.866
It's cold.

52:56.361 --> 52:59.782
It's just that you were crying…

53:00.282 --> 53:03.327
It's just drool.

53:04.036 --> 53:07.121
Let's go.

53:07.122 --> 53:08.999
All right.

53:11.168 --> 53:12.336
The GPS…

53:15.047 --> 53:16.589
Wait.

53:16.590 --> 53:17.882
Seongsu-dong?

53:25.641 --> 53:27.059
Was I mistaken?

53:28.185 --> 53:31.772
Did you go to Seongsu-dong last Thursday?

53:32.815 --> 53:34.441
You were with Grandma, right?

53:35.108 --> 53:37.193
- No. I'll start the car.
- Wait.

53:37.194 --> 53:39.111
I saw Grandma that day.

53:39.112 --> 53:41.323
I'm sure I saw her crying.

53:42.199 --> 53:44.116
She was crying?

53:44.117 --> 53:45.911
So you did go to Seongsu-dong, right?

53:47.913 --> 53:49.623
That woke me right up.

53:51.959 --> 53:53.085
Is something going on?

53:54.670 --> 53:56.128
What is it?

53:56.129 --> 53:58.465
I'm sorry, but just let this go for now.

53:59.800 --> 54:00.968
Please.

54:26.159 --> 54:28.536
MISSING ELDERLY WITH DEMENTIA

54:33.584 --> 54:36.085
You can't stop looking at it.
Are you that impressed?

54:36.086 --> 54:37.879
Are you sure I really made this?

54:37.880 --> 54:39.881
Did you make it again
because it was a mess?

54:39.882 --> 54:41.717
Of course not.

54:42.426 --> 54:46.387
I'd love to have dinner with you,
but I'm meeting the people who helped me.

54:46.388 --> 54:49.765
I'll stay in Seoul for a few days,
so let's have a meal sometime.

54:49.766 --> 54:51.892
And bring your mother's dish then.

54:51.893 --> 54:53.269
All right.

54:53.270 --> 54:55.646
Her mother's dish? What do you mean?

54:55.647 --> 54:57.898
Why are you curious about everything?

54:57.899 --> 55:00.318
Grandma, don't do that in front of her.

55:00.319 --> 55:01.736
Your cheeks are so squishy.

55:05.365 --> 55:06.700
The weather's so nice.

55:07.284 --> 55:08.534
How about dinner--

55:08.535 --> 55:10.329
Sorry, but you should go home first.

55:11.038 --> 55:13.040
- I'll see you later.
- Where are you going?

55:13.582 --> 55:14.833
Ms. Song!

55:16.835 --> 55:19.670
Being overly polite
will hurt her feelings.

55:19.671 --> 55:22.299
But I should at least give her
some hand lotion.

55:23.967 --> 55:24.968
Huh?

55:29.723 --> 55:31.308
Oh? Did she leave?

55:32.809 --> 55:33.810
Hang on.

55:37.356 --> 55:39.231
- She's not here?
- Did she leave?

55:39.232 --> 55:40.650
We can come back…

55:43.028 --> 55:44.111
Hmm?

55:50.535 --> 55:52.286
Dad. Dad!

55:52.287 --> 55:54.331
What more do I have to do
to make you stop?

55:59.336 --> 56:00.753
Let's just go.

56:00.754 --> 56:03.131
- Wait, I…
-  Chan.

56:07.511 --> 56:09.513
You're back.

56:10.180 --> 56:13.224
He had business nearby

56:13.225 --> 56:16.895
and dropped by to greet me
when he saw the sign.

56:20.148 --> 56:21.274
It's been a while.

56:23.568 --> 56:26.529
There was
an international conference nearby.

56:26.530 --> 56:27.531
Your school…

56:28.198 --> 56:32.451
No, your former school
and some other schools--

56:32.452 --> 56:34.120
That's enough.

56:34.121 --> 56:35.539
I'm not even curious.

56:37.249 --> 56:39.000
- Let's go.
- How are you?

56:39.668 --> 56:41.753
How is your condition these days?

56:50.721 --> 56:51.847
Are you going somewhere?

56:55.350 --> 56:56.685
Why are you taking your passport?

56:57.519 --> 56:59.146
I don't want to stay in Korea.

56:59.730 --> 57:01.481
You made a good decision.

57:02.607 --> 57:06.444
You received enough treatment,
so you can return to school--

57:06.445 --> 57:07.863
I'm not…

57:08.864 --> 57:10.197
going back to school.

57:10.198 --> 57:11.491
I'm not studying anymore.

57:12.993 --> 57:15.162
What? You've already wasted so much time.

57:16.163 --> 57:19.583
Are you going to give up everything
just because of some accident?

57:20.083 --> 57:23.627
Stop acting like a child
and be reasonable.

57:23.628 --> 57:26.965
You should finish your master's
and move on to a PhD program…

57:27.591 --> 57:28.925
Do you not see me?

57:30.510 --> 57:34.306
I'm covered in burn scars,
and I can't hear on one side.

57:35.265 --> 57:37.684
- You call that "some accident"?
- It's in the past.

57:38.185 --> 57:39.810
Blaming it won't change anything.

57:39.811 --> 57:42.230
Enough with the pathetic self-pity!

57:46.985 --> 57:48.069
I get it now.

57:48.904 --> 57:52.406
This is why she left you.
It was because of you.

57:52.407 --> 57:54.159
She didn't just leave,

57:54.993 --> 57:56.494
you made her leave!

57:56.495 --> 57:58.329
I'll leave too.

57:58.330 --> 58:00.040
I'll live my own life,

58:00.582 --> 58:04.210
so just think
that your stupid, obedient son…

58:06.922 --> 58:08.048
died…

58:09.257 --> 58:11.176
in that explosion.

58:18.850 --> 58:20.184
Why are you acting like this?

58:20.185 --> 58:22.645
You never worried about me before.

58:25.315 --> 58:27.150
I saw you here earlier,

58:27.859 --> 58:31.655
so I left,
in case you'd feel uncomfortable.

58:33.114 --> 58:35.074
I didn't know you'd come back.

58:35.075 --> 58:36.159
You're right.

58:36.785 --> 58:38.452
I do feel uncomfortable.

58:38.453 --> 58:41.915
So if you ever see me anywhere again,

58:42.457 --> 58:43.541
don't even say hi.

58:43.542 --> 58:45.334
Chan, don't do this!

58:45.335 --> 58:47.920
Are you going to keep acting
like you're strangers?

58:47.921 --> 58:49.840
Since you've met… Hmm?

58:50.632 --> 58:52.300
Give her the flowers. I'm leaving.

58:54.094 --> 58:55.803
- Chan, let's talk--
- Stop!

59:11.862 --> 59:13.237
Chan! Don't. Stop.

59:13.238 --> 59:15.114
Let him go! Let go of him!

59:15.115 --> 59:16.282
Let him go.

59:16.283 --> 59:17.783
Don't do this!

59:17.784 --> 59:20.160
Chan, let him go!

59:20.161 --> 59:23.206
Go. Everyone, just go!

59:34.509 --> 59:36.344
Oh, dear. Let me see.

59:36.970 --> 59:38.263
Oh, no.

59:38.722 --> 59:39.805
I'm sorry.

59:39.806 --> 59:43.018
It's okay.
I didn't even notice. I'm really fine.

59:44.060 --> 59:46.980
Grandma, take care of her for me.

59:48.648 --> 59:50.108
Wait…

59:51.943 --> 59:53.236
He won't be able…

59:54.487 --> 59:56.281
to face you right now.

01:00:14.549 --> 01:00:16.801
Darn it…

01:00:29.439 --> 01:00:31.983
I'll be able to fix the shattered pottery,

01:00:33.485 --> 01:00:36.529
but I can't do anything
about their relationship.

01:00:37.530 --> 01:00:39.991
They've had a deep rift for a long time.

01:00:44.496 --> 01:00:46.163
You can take it.

01:00:46.164 --> 01:00:47.832
Sorry, hang on.

01:00:48.458 --> 01:00:49.793
Yes, Director.

01:00:50.794 --> 01:00:51.877
Yes.

01:00:51.878 --> 01:00:53.505
Of course.

01:01:02.347 --> 01:01:05.141
PROFESSOR SUNWOO SEOK

01:01:06.017 --> 01:01:07.394
"Science University"?

01:01:09.729 --> 01:01:11.105
From the smell,

01:01:11.106 --> 01:01:13.524
it seemed like
diluted sodium hypochlorite solution.

01:01:13.525 --> 01:01:16.194
Because of the diffraction of sunlight,
the cloud particles…

01:01:16.695 --> 01:01:18.154
Petrichor.

01:01:18.780 --> 01:01:20.948
Your former school
and some other schools…

01:01:20.949 --> 01:01:22.616
I guess
you majored in that field.

01:01:22.617 --> 01:01:24.660
It seems like
you majored in engineering.

01:01:24.661 --> 01:01:27.079
He never tells me
what he did before entering CalArts.

01:01:27.080 --> 01:01:28.790
I lived like a corpse.

01:01:42.220 --> 01:01:44.680
Laundry…

01:01:44.681 --> 01:01:45.932
Is there any laundry?

01:01:59.654 --> 01:02:02.197
What happened to the pen you always use?

01:02:02.198 --> 01:02:04.158
I lost it, and I never found it.

01:02:04.159 --> 01:02:05.660
I'll just use a new one now.

01:02:06.536 --> 01:02:07.871
It's nothing special.

01:02:09.080 --> 01:02:10.081
Wait.

01:02:10.790 --> 01:02:12.834
Why is this pen here?

01:02:18.631 --> 01:02:20.175
Huh? Genius.

01:02:25.555 --> 01:02:27.057
Mr. Seonu.

01:02:27.932 --> 01:02:29.558
Oh? You're in here.

01:02:29.559 --> 01:02:31.810
Yes, I was collecting laundry.

01:02:31.811 --> 01:02:34.271
But why did you come upstairs?

01:02:34.272 --> 01:02:36.315
Sorry, I came without asking.

01:02:36.316 --> 01:02:39.359
I just wanted to see Mr. Seonu.
I have something to give him.

01:02:39.360 --> 01:02:41.361
He hasn't come home yet.

01:02:41.362 --> 01:02:42.946
Let's go. I'll make you coffee.

01:02:42.947 --> 01:02:44.532
- Okay.
- All right.

01:02:47.077 --> 01:02:48.369
What happened?

01:02:49.204 --> 01:02:50.621
Did you get hurt?

01:02:50.622 --> 01:02:52.414
It's just a small scratch.

01:02:52.415 --> 01:02:53.624
Let's go on a walk.

01:02:53.625 --> 01:02:55.584
Let's go on a walk.

01:02:55.585 --> 01:02:58.462
We didn't get to go
on a walk today.

01:02:58.463 --> 01:03:00.672
You can go. I don't need coffee.

01:03:00.673 --> 01:03:02.591
I'll wait here for Mr. Seonu.

01:03:02.592 --> 01:03:03.635
Are you sure?

01:03:05.011 --> 01:03:06.595
Hey, Haran…

01:03:06.596 --> 01:03:09.057
About before…

01:03:10.100 --> 01:03:11.476
No, never mind.

01:03:12.060 --> 01:03:13.852
I'll be back soon.

01:03:13.853 --> 01:03:15.063
Wait a moment.

01:03:15.605 --> 01:03:18.900
cafe SHIM

01:03:22.278 --> 01:03:23.613
Why isn't he coming?

01:03:28.743 --> 01:03:30.077
Oh?

01:03:30.078 --> 01:03:31.079
You're here.

01:03:40.255 --> 01:03:42.215
Where have you been this whole…

01:03:43.800 --> 01:03:46.260
Let's go inside. You look exhausted.

01:03:46.261 --> 01:03:47.595
I'm sorry.

01:03:48.179 --> 01:03:49.722
For leaving like that

01:03:50.598 --> 01:03:52.433
and for hurting you.

01:03:54.018 --> 01:03:55.228
It's okay.

01:03:56.229 --> 01:03:57.814
I'm totally fine.

01:03:59.315 --> 01:04:00.525
It's all my fault.

01:04:01.067 --> 01:04:05.737
I was being selfish,
trying to stay by your side.

01:04:05.738 --> 01:04:06.823
What are you saying?

01:04:07.490 --> 01:04:09.868
Just make me some tea
instead of saying such nonsense.

01:04:25.884 --> 01:04:27.886
I've been thinking…

01:04:28.928 --> 01:04:33.849
I don't think it's a good idea
for us to be this close, so--

01:04:33.850 --> 01:04:35.101
You saw this, right?

01:04:35.727 --> 01:04:38.146
Wow. I was so surprised when I saw it.

01:04:39.314 --> 01:04:42.900
These lines are where she mended
the broken pieces.

01:04:42.901 --> 01:04:45.236
Don't they make this look more beautiful?

01:04:45.987 --> 01:04:48.615
It seems admirable, too.

01:04:49.199 --> 01:04:51.075
- Ms. Song.
- To me…

01:04:54.037 --> 01:04:55.455
you're these lines.

01:04:58.333 --> 01:04:59.626
Ms. Song!

01:05:02.545 --> 01:05:03.922
The first snow…

01:05:05.298 --> 01:05:06.465
Vapor trails…

01:05:06.466 --> 01:05:08.259
Wow, it's beautiful.

01:05:09.052 --> 01:05:10.553
Jamsugyo…

01:05:11.304 --> 01:05:13.514
And a certain name…

01:05:14.432 --> 01:05:17.852
They were all sad memories,
so I thought I'd never get over them.

01:05:18.603 --> 01:05:21.522
But I found myself feeling okay,

01:05:22.523 --> 01:05:24.192
thanks to someone

01:05:25.193 --> 01:05:27.445
who covered them with good memories.

01:05:28.947 --> 01:05:32.492
But you say something like that
over a tiny scratch?

01:05:34.369 --> 01:05:36.537
It's a relief I met you here.

01:05:38.289 --> 01:05:40.500
Thanks to you, I found a way,

01:05:41.084 --> 01:05:44.545
so this time, why don't you try it…

01:05:46.506 --> 01:05:47.548
with your father?

01:05:50.426 --> 01:05:51.844
That's impossible.

01:05:54.889 --> 01:05:56.683
You remember when we first met, right?

01:05:57.517 --> 01:06:00.353
I was cold and avoided you.

01:06:01.145 --> 01:06:03.690
I thought it was impossible too.

01:06:04.274 --> 01:06:08.444
But I guess there's no such thing
as never in a relationship.

01:06:09.195 --> 01:06:11.906
Aren't I a good example of that?

01:06:17.578 --> 01:06:19.539
I picked this up at the exhibit.

01:06:21.207 --> 01:06:23.208
He must wear this all the time.

01:06:23.209 --> 01:06:24.794
It's in the photo as well.

01:06:29.215 --> 01:06:30.424
I've never seen it before.

01:06:30.425 --> 01:06:31.634
Really?

01:06:32.510 --> 01:06:36.180
The drawing here looks similar
to the one I saw at your grandma's place.

01:06:42.770 --> 01:06:46.607
He must have kept wearing it
even when it was broken.

01:06:48.693 --> 01:06:50.528
I bought that for him a long time ago

01:06:51.654 --> 01:06:53.323
at a stationary store

01:06:54.532 --> 01:06:55.992
for Parents' Day.

01:06:56.951 --> 01:06:58.244
Maybe…

01:06:59.078 --> 01:07:01.247
he wanted to mend things.

01:07:01.831 --> 01:07:04.459
He's been wearing this broken watch
the whole time.

01:07:16.888 --> 01:07:18.848
I should give you some time alone.

01:07:23.770 --> 01:07:24.937
Thank you.

01:07:33.738 --> 01:07:38.534
I have a habit
of hugging people I want to comfort.

01:07:39.744 --> 01:07:41.329
That's my thing.

01:07:42.830 --> 01:07:44.165
Why do you keep copying me?

01:07:47.585 --> 01:07:50.338
I wish we'd met earlier.

01:07:51.214 --> 01:07:54.300
Then we could've gotten close faster,
and I would've been nicer first.

01:07:55.760 --> 01:07:58.345
I would have at least given you a hug

01:07:58.346 --> 01:08:01.224
when you were scared to open your eyes.

01:08:10.733 --> 01:08:14.111
You saved me as well.

01:08:21.411 --> 01:08:24.747
You already did that for me.

01:08:41.389 --> 01:08:46.978
Genius, you know
that Haran should become happy, right?

01:08:47.770 --> 01:08:52.357
The fact that I lived
while he died from that accident…

01:08:52.358 --> 01:08:54.192
Her boyfriend died back then.

01:08:54.193 --> 01:08:56.778
He went to study in Boston,
but he suddenly died.

01:09:02.034 --> 01:09:06.038
"Newbury Street, Boston?"

01:09:15.590 --> 01:09:17.467
I've only
received things from you.

01:09:21.471 --> 01:09:23.389
I should be really nice to you
from now on.

01:09:27.101 --> 01:09:28.144
Then…

01:09:31.063 --> 01:09:32.815
I might end up liking you even more.

01:09:33.441 --> 01:09:34.984
It's okay…

01:09:36.319 --> 01:09:37.445
if you like me more.

01:09:39.614 --> 01:09:40.823
If I like you more…

01:09:44.702 --> 01:09:46.162
I might get more greedy.

01:09:49.665 --> 01:09:50.708
It's okay

01:09:51.959 --> 01:09:53.419
if you get more greedy.

01:10:46.138 --> 01:10:48.139
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:11:12.164 --> 01:11:16.293
Why do you keep saying
it's greedy to like me?

01:11:16.294 --> 01:11:18.753
-  You mean it, right?
-  Yes.

01:11:18.754 --> 01:11:22.841
How about letting time
with your dad start moving again?

01:11:22.842 --> 01:11:24.759
The past is the past,

01:11:24.760 --> 01:11:28.221
and what matters is the time you have now.

01:11:28.222 --> 01:11:30.765
There's nothing wrong with her, right?

01:11:30.766 --> 01:11:34.144
What on earth is happening to you?

01:11:34.145 --> 01:11:37.105
Seonu Chan found this pen for you.

01:11:37.106 --> 01:11:39.566
And this is a lucky charm.

01:11:39.567 --> 01:11:42.403
No way. What is this?

01:11:56.375 --> 01:11:57.459
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:11:57.460 --> 01:11:58.461
Translated by Juyoung Park
